    "content": "Letter Directives BookOpen Two inline directives handle letter display in Lexora: :letter for a single styled card, and :letterGrid for a full script chart. Both render on blue boards that match the reference screenshots. :letter — Single Letter Card Place one letter inside a styled card. The glyph goes between square brackets; all options go in curly braces. Card Options Parameter Required Values Default transliteration no IAST string — meaning no any hint text — size no small normal big normal highlight no true \\ false false Size Examples अ a short open vowel आ ā long open vowel इ i as in 'sit' Highlight Passing highlight=\"true\" adds an accent colour background. Use it to call out the most important letter on the page. अ a as in 'about' आ ā as in 'father' With Tamil or Meaning Hints The meaning attribute accepts any short text, including a Tamil pronunciation hint: ऋ ṛ like ரி in ரிஷி — syllabic r ळ ḷa like ள in குளம் (pond) ऴ ẓa like ழ in பழம் (fruit) Using :letter Inside a Table Cards work inside Markdown tables because they are inline elements: Short Long Difference अ a आ ā hold the sound longer इ i ई ī hold the sound longer :letterGrid — Script Chart Board Renders a full grid of letters inside a blue board. The title appears top right; letters flow through the grid in the order you write them. Grid Options Parameter Required Values Default items yes comma separated glyph=translit pairs — rows no number 4 cols no number — layout no inline stack inline variant no board plain board Items Format Every item is a glyph=transliteration pair. Separate pairs with commas. Prefix any item with to highlight its glyph in yellow : Add an optional Tamil pronunciation after a pipe as a third field: The Tamil text renders in a smaller muted colour below the transliteration, wrapped in parentheses. Items with no = part are shown with only the glyph. Example with all three fields: Visarga ः अः aḥ அஹ आः āḥ ஆஹ इः iḥ இஹ ईः īḥ ஈஹ उः uḥ உஹ ऊः ūḥ ஊஹ Layout Modes Column major: rows=\"N\" (default) Items fill top to bottom , then wrap to the next column. Best for vowel charts. The vowel board on the Vowels lesson uses rows=\"4\": Vowels अ a आ ā इ i ई ī उ u ऊ ū ऋ ṛ ॠ ṝ ऌ ḷ ॡ ḹ ए e ऐ ai ओ o औ au अं aṃ अः aḥ Row major: cols=\"N\" Items fill left to right , then wrap to the next row. Best for consonant grids. Setting cols=\"5\" keeps five letters per row: Consonants क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ च c छ ch ज j झ jh ञ ñ Stack Layout: layout=\"stack\" In stack mode the glyph appears above its transliteration instead of beside it. This matches the consonant chart style from the reference images. Combine with cols for a row major stacked board: Consonants क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ च c छ ch ज j झ jh ञ ñ ट ṭ ठ ṭh ड ḍ ढ ḍh ण ṇ त t थ th द d ध dh न n प p फ ph ब b भ bh म m Compare default layout=\"inline\" with the same data: Consonants क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ Highlight with Prefix any item with to render its glyph in yellow on a board, or in the accent colour on a plain board. The consonant chart uses this to mark the nasal at the end of each group: Nasals highlighted क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ Without : No highlight क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ Plain Variant: variant=\"plain\" Use variant=\"plain\" to remove the blue background and render on the page surface instead. Useful for inline reference tables or light theme sections: Plain board क k ख kh ग g घ gh ङ ṅ च c छ ch ज j झ jh ञ ñ Tips Use :letter inside paragraphs or table cells when you need an inline card. Use :letterGrid when you want a standalone reference board. cols + layout=\"stack\" → consonant chart style (stacked, row major). rows + default layout=\"inline\" → vowel chart style (side by side, column major). on any item highlights that letter in yellow — traditional use is the nasal at the end of each consonant group.",
